## FFMx Correlation Notes

> FFMx = (A × Q × E^k) / T.  Higher Q from v2.0-templated renders directly lifts
> the FFMx numerator.  To measure per-version FFMx delta:
>
> ```bash
> python3 scripts/7x_ffmx_calculator.py \
>   --manifests-dir forensics/manifests/YYYY-MM-DD \
>   --investigation-label honey-version-sync
> ```
>
> Compare Q averages in the **Version Comparison** table above for a quick proxy.
> v2.0-templated should show higher Q than v1.0-static if templating improves
> context quality and agent self-awareness.

## Mutation Classification

| Transition | Type | Evidence Required |
|------------|------|------------------|
| v1.0-static → v2.0-templated | Positive Emergence candidate | Q delta ≥+0.05 sustained ≥3 days |
| Quality regression | Negative Emergence | Q drops below 0.70 for any version |
| Audience expansion | Neutral Emergence | New audiences appear in rendering_context |

